title.@value: Intentional self-harm, not known or not determined if person intended to die

definition.@value: Information that a competent person (e.g. psychiatrist, coroner) had concluded that it could not be determined whether the intentional self-harm was done with intent to die. No information or insufficient information was available.

label.@value: Intentional self-harm, not known or not determined if person intended to die
